25|$|The {{most common}} {{infectious}} disease in <b>gerbils</b> is Tyzzer's disease, a bacterial disease, which stress can make animals more susceptible to. It produces {{symptoms such as}} ruffled fur, lethargy, hunched posture, poor appetite, diarrhoea, and often death. It quickly spreads between <b>gerbils</b> in close contact.|$|E
