50|$|Burton's <b>gerbil,</b> Gerbillus burtoni is {{distributed}} mainly in Darfur, Sudan. Less than 250 individuals {{of this species}} of <b>gerbil</b> are thought to persist in the wild. It may have been named after Edward Burton, who had the <b>gerbil</b> in his menagerie, obtained from Darfur and described by Frédéric Cuvier.|$|R
